episodes.title: The Noise That Blue Makes
episodes.plot: Ardal O'Hanlon, Bridget Christie, Chris Ramsey, Judi Love and Sophie Duker enter Greg Davies' lair to begin a bitter battle for glory. Alex Horne invigilates while trying to avoid a barrage of fruit.

episodes.title: Birdy Hand Finger
episodes.plot: Greg Davies' personal valet Alex Horne diligently notes the facts and figures as Ardal O'Hanlon makes some sheep, Chris Ramsey gets younger, Judi Love becomes a queen and Bridget Christie gets lost in a small field.

episodes.title: I Think I've Got This
episodes.plot: Bridget Christie shoves a cuddly toy inside a traffic cone, Sophie Duker does a dinosaur impression, Ardal O'Hanlon is defeated by a robot, Chris Ramsey is impressed with a hose, and Judi Love is confident about everything except marbles.

episodes.title: Shoe Who
episodes.plot: The contestants must pick which shoe is Alex's with only yes or no questions.

episodes.title: Having a Little Chuckle
episodes.plot: The comics are baffled by high fives and a fish tank. Bridget Christie has a present for the Taskmaster, and Sophie Duker covers some keys in saliva.

episodes.title: The 75th Question
episodes.plot: The contestants present new uses for a cement mixer, count their steps, and gather for a very dramatic meeting.

episodes.title: Heg
episodes.plot: Ardal O'Hanlon indulges in a plant-based snack, liquids are poured down a giant tube on Sophie Duker's head, Chris Ramsey refuses to consume dried spaghetti and Bridget Christie browns a bun.

episodes.title: You Tuper Super
episodes.plot: Ardal sings about leaning on a fence, Judi Love designs some classy headgear, Sophie Duker displays genuinely world-class levels of endurance and fortitude, Chris Ramsey finds he can still fit into Alex Horne's horrible slip-on shoes.

episodes.title: It Might Be Wind
episodes.plot: Chris Ramsey surprises everyone, Bridget Christie doesn't know what a cup is, and Ardal O'Hanlon has some fun with yoghurt.

episodes.title: The House Queens
episodes.plot: The teams get musical, some liquids are available for tasting and the contestant flatter themselves through art.
